comments.body: During the retrospective meeting on 05/29, this was given a higher priority.
This is really only blocked by the need to perform testing for the production server.

I ended up creating the following `irbd` and `jrubyd` aliases which may be useful

```bash
alias irbd=‚Äúirb -I /usr/local/src/jruby-projects/dspace-jruby/lib -I /usr/local/src/jruby-projects/dspace-cli‚Äù
alias jrubyd=‚Äújruby -I /usr/local/src/jruby-projects/dspace-jruby/lib -I /usr/local/src/jruby-projects/dspace-cli‚Äù
```

This should be ready to be merged. Unfortunately, the runlevel issue is actually due to the fact that the base image for the Docker container does not have `systemd` installed. SysVinit is instead used, and attempting to install `systemd` atop of this requires a reboot (one cannot really support this for a Docker provisioning pipeline).

research-data-harvester.title: Research and document harvesting from Dimensions

comments.body: I generated a token and put it in LastPass in `dimensions_api_token`.

Query for publications will be something like:

```
search publications where research_org_names ="Princeton University" or research_orgs="grid.16750.35" return publications[all]
```

and datasets:
```
search datasets where research_orgs="grid.16750.35" return datasets[all]
```

The response is verbose("all"), but that can be tailored. Next step is to figure out paging.

For paging, use `limit` for page size and `skip` for offset.

```
search datasets where research_orgs="grid.16750.35"
return datasets[all] limit 100 skip 100
```

Total record count is returned in each request in the `_stats` property:

```
 "_stats": {
        "total_count": 1916,
        "limit": 100,
        "offset": 100
    }
```
